<div id="review_2235728881" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2235728881" />
    <a title="Scott  Hitchcock" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50894754-scott-hitchcock"><img alt="Scott  Hitchcock" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459187975p2/50894754.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2235728881?book_show_action=true">Jan 01, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Scott  Hitchcock" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Scott  Hitchcock" href="/user/show/50894754-scott-hitchcock">Scott  Hitchcock</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook " href="/book/show/18584714-the-drawing-of-the-three">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50894754-scott-hitchcock?shelf=abandoned-series">abandoned-series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50894754-scott-hitchcock?shelf=horror">horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2235728881" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12428689199606150304">Book 1: 2.5*<br/>Book 2: 2.5*<br/><br/>The dichotomy that is this series. On the one hand I want to know how it turns out. On the other I don&apos;t think I can do another book with senseless rants, non stop nostalgic pop culture references, stereotypes ad nauseam and a storyline that meanders aimlessly. <br/><br/>The characters are all tough to like. Not because they have flaws but because they all have non sequitur inane ramblings that drive the reader to the brink of the craziness which drives the characters. <br/><br/>I simply can</span>
  <span id="freeText12428689199606150304" style="display:none">Book 1: 2.5*<br />Book 2: 2.5*<br /><br />The dichotomy that is this series. On the one hand I want to know how it turns out. On the other I don't think I can do another book with senseless rants, non stop nostalgic pop culture references, stereotypes ad nauseam and a storyline that meanders aimlessly. <br /><br />The characters are all tough to like. Not because they have flaws but because they all have non sequitur inane ramblings that drive the reader to the brink of the craziness which drives the characters. <br /><br />I simply cannot continue this series. Maybe I'll read a summary just to find out but overall it's just a waste of time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12428689199606150304" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


